Sipping his tea, Nick said the water is quantity is very low last year and people are hardly getting any water to take from the public taps. Most people either use Poly tanks or are digging their own wells to access water when not enough rain falls.

Speaking in reference to the water situation in the last 5 years, Nick said there was an improvement in the amount of rain in the last 5 years, following new developments in their energy source such as the use of Mega Solar. But that wasn’t enough.

He said there’s problem in the water supply to the public. For this reason, a group of I-Kiribati started to lobby the government in August 2016, raising the issues but to no avail. No positive response had been given, he said, insisting the situation of water stress continue to deteriorate.

However, Nick was optimistic that there is still hope that the problems of the country will be solved. He blamed high population growth, government decision to take houses near the seashores, and the reluctance of government bureaucrats to acknowledge the reality of climate change, as the causes of current issues.

(Kiribati, 16 Oct,'17)
